:[{"name":"Huett","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Somerset): variant of   Hewitt  .","German (<b>Hütt</b>): status name for someone living in a hut or owning a small shop, Middle High German <i>hütte</i>, or a habitational name from any of several places called Hütt or Hütte. Compare   Hutt  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Hitt","meanings":["Americanized form of German <b>Hütt</b> (see   Huett  ).","German: occupational name in Westphalia for a goat dealer, from dialect <i>hitte</i> ‘goat’.","English (Devon): apparently a variant of   Hett  ; see   Hatt  ."]},{"name":"Hotte","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Lucien, Adelard, Adrien, Jacques, Marcel, Pierrette.","French: from <i>hotte</i>, denoting a type of basket carried on the back, hence a nickname or a metonymic occupational name for someone who carried or made these.","German (<b>Hötte</b>): variant of <b>Hütte</b> (see   Huett   2) or a variant of   Hott  ."]},{"name":"Huetter","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Gerhard, Heinz, Kurt.","German (<b>Hütter</b>):","variant of <b>Hütt</b> (see   Huett   2), with the addition of the agent suffix <i>-er</i>."]},{"name":"Huettl","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Alfons, Erhard, Othmar.","South German (<b>Hüttl</b>): diminutive of <b>Hütt</b> (see   Huett   2)."]},{"name":"Hewitt","meanings":["English:","from the Middle English personal name <i>Hewet</i>, <i>Huet</i>, <i>Hughet</i>, <i>Howet</i>, pet forms of <i>Hugh</i> (Middle English <i>Hewe</i>, <i>Hue</i>; see   Hugh   and compare   Hew  ). The spelling <i>Hughet</i> stood for both <i>Huet</i> and the synonymous <i>Huget</i>; see   Huggett  . This surname has also been established in Ireland since the 14th century.","habitational name from Hewitts in Chelsfield or Hewitts in Willesborough (both Kent), both named from Old English <i>hīewett</i> ‘cutting’, denoting a place where trees had been cut down. Here there lived families called <i>de la Hewatte</i> (1270), <i>de la hewett</i> (1301), and <i>atte Hewete</i> (1338). The name may also be topographic for someone who lived in a newly made clearing in a wood."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":60,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"John Huett was born in 1395, in Northamptonshire, England. He had at least 1 son. He died in 1490, in his hometown, at the age of 95."},"et":{"1395–1490":"1395–1490","1421–1500":"1421–1500","1500":"1500","1455":"1455","1421":"1421","1395":"1395","1490":"1490","Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, England"},"fi":{"1395–1490":"1395–1490","1421–1500":"1421–1500","1500":"1500","1455":"1455","1421":"1421","1395":"1395","1490":"1490","Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, England"},"fr":{"1395–1490":"1395–1490","1421–1500":"1421–1500","1500":"1500","1455":"1455","1421":"1421","1395":"1395","1490":"1490","Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"John Huett est né en 1395, à Northamptonshire, Angleterre. Il a eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé en 1490, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 95 ans."},"de":{"1395–1490":"1395–1490","1421–1500":"1421–1500","1500":"1500","1455":"1455","1421":"1421","1395":"1395","1490":"1490","Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, England","lifeSummary":"John Huett wurde 1395 in Nor